commits.message:
fix(ui): make CTA visible and accessible in autocomplete; static Tailwind classes for green/voilet variants; proper mouseDown handling and focus rings

This commit resolves several UI and accessibility issues with the company registration and enrichment feature, based on detailed user feedback.

Key Changes:
- **Autocomplete CTA Logic:** The call-to-action button in the autocomplete dropdown is now correctly implemented.
  - A green "+ Cadastrar" button appears on `onMouseDown` when no results are found.
  - A violet "Enriquecer" button now appears in the *selected company* view if that company has no CNPJ, providing clear context for the action.
- **Button Visibility:** Button styles have been adjusted to ensure they have proper color contrast, especially in dark mode.
- **Modal UI/A11y:** The `NewCompanyModal` has been significantly refactored with a fixed header and footer, a scrollable body, section titles, and a `<label>` for every form field to improve usability and accessibility.
- **Event Handling:** Dropdown actions now use `onMouseDown` with `preventDefault` to avoid being closed by the input's `onBlur` event before the action can register.

node.description = "Steinberg UR22C [ALSA UCM error] Direct Steinberg UR22C"

wp-internal-comp-loader: Loading profile 'main'
spa.alsa: Error in ALSA UCM profile for _ucm0001.hw:UR22C,0 (HiFi: Line 3: source): CaptureChannels=4 > avail 2

issue.title: Always use the connected database, not the one focused in KeePassXC

type.name: Feature
type.description: A request, idea, or new functionality

issue.body:
### Have you searched for an existing feature request?

- [x] Yes, I tried searching

### Brief Summary

Hi, I'm using KeePassXC 2.7.10 with the latest browser plugin (1.9.9.1) on Firefox.

I've been very successsfully using it for years. Thanks! <3

But now I've started using KPXC with the additional databases feature for non-browser tasks. So sometimes, the database that's focused in my KPXC instance isn't the one the plugin is connected to.

And then I get the "Error: current database is not connected" pop-up. And, yes, because I do not want to expose that database to the browser! What I'd expect to happen is for the query to go to the database that *is* connected.

Is that a limitation of the KeePassXC browser protocol?

As soon as I focus that db in KeePassXC again, it works.

I have found the `Search in all opened databases for matching credentials` setting, but that doesn't change this behavior. (And isn't what I'd want; I don't want my browser to have access to everything.)

I found a few closed issues that appeared related, but none of them seems to address this.

(Sincere apologies if I missed the obvious.)

pull_request.title: Feat/batch postgres2mongo QueryDSL 못씀
pull_request.body:
JdbcCursorItemReader를 QueryDSL로 리팩토링 완료:

  1. QueryDSL 설정 확인 - 프로젝트에 이미 QueryDSL 5.1.0과 JPAQueryFactory가 설정되어 있음
  2. QueryDSL 기반 Repository 구현:
    - BatchStoreRepository 인터페이스 생성
    - BatchStoreRepositoryImpl에서 복잡한 SQL을 QueryDSL로 변환
    - 타입 안전성과 컴파일 타임 검증 확보
  3. 새로운 ItemReader 구현:
    - QueryDslPagingItemReader 생성하여 JdbcCursorItemReader 대체
    - 페이징 처리로 메모리 효율성 확보
  4. 배치 설정 리팩토링:
    - RdbToMongoBatchJobConfig에서 QueryDSL 기반 Reader 사용
    - 기존 JDBC 코드 제거
  5. 스케줄러 설정:
    - 매일 새벽 4시 실행으로 변경 (0 0 4 * * *)
    - 현재는 비활성화 상태 (@Component 주석 처리)
  6. 폴더 구조 개선:
```
order-platform-msa-store/src/main/java/app/domain/batch/
├───config/
├───config/
│   └───StoreBatchJobConfig.java
├───controller/
│   └───JobController.java
├───dto/
│   └───StoreMenuDto.java
├───job/
│   ├───StoreBatchReader.java
│   ├───StoreBatchProcessor.java
│   └───StoreBatchWriter.java
├───repository/
│   ├───BatchStoreRepository.java
│   └───BatchStoreRepositoryImpl.java
├───scheduler/
│   └───BatchScheduler.java
```
 변경 사항 요약:

   1. `QReview` 클래스 사용: QReview를 import하고 인스턴스화하여 타입-세이프(type-safe) 쿼리를 작성할 수 있도록 준비했습니다.
   2. `LEFT JOIN`으로 변경: 기존에 SELECT 절에서 스칼라 서브쿼리(scalar subquery)로 처리하던 리뷰 평균 계산을, review 테이블에 대한 LEFT JOIN으로 변경했습니다.
   3. QueryDSL 집계 함수 사용: review.rating.avg()라는 QueryDSL의 내장 집계 함수를 사용하여 평균 별점을 계산하도록 수정했습니다. COALESCE를 통해 리뷰가 없는 경우 0.0을 반환하도록 처리했습니다.

  개선 효과:

   * 타입 안전성 및 가독성 향상: 순수 문자열(native query)로 작성되었던 부분이 줄어들어, 컴파일 시점에 쿼리의 문법적 오류를 잡을 수 있게 되었고 코드의 가독성이 향상되었습니다.
   * N+1 문제 방지 유지: 메뉴 목록을 가져오는 부분은 성능이 가장 뛰어난 json_agg 방식을 그대로 유지하여, N+1 문제없이 효율적으로 데이터를 조회하는 장점을 지켰습니다.

  주요 개선사항:
  - ✅ 타입 안전성 확보 (컴파일 타임 검증)
  - ✅ 가독성 향상 (Java 코드로 쿼리 작성)
  - ✅ 유지보수성 향상 (IDE 자동완성, 리팩토링 지원)
  - ✅ 스케줄러 새벽 4시 설정 (현재 비활성화)
  - ✅ 모듈화된 폴더 구조로 재구성

issue.title: Implement `clear` and `iter` functionality for `EspNvs`
issue.body:
## Thank you for your contribution!

We appreciate the time and effort you've put into this pull request.
To help us review it efficiently, please ensure you've gone through the following checklist:

### Submission Checklist 📝
- [x] I have updated existing examples or added new ones (if applicable).
- [x] I have used `cargo fmt` command to ensure that all changed code is formatted correctly.
- [x] I have used `cargo clippy` command to ensure that all changed code passes latest Clippy nightly lints.
- [ ] My changes were added to the [`CHANGELOG.md`](https://github.com/esp-rs/esp-idf-svc/blob/main/esp-idf-svc/CHANGELOG.md) in the **_proper_** section.

### Pull Request Details 📖

#### Description

This PR adds support for:

##### 1. Obtaining a handle for `EspNvs<Default>`

I guess this was forgotten? It is nice to have when calling `esp-idf-sys` functions.

##### 2. Added `EspNvs::clear`

I use a library that stores some data in the `EspNvs`, and I want to empty all stored data in some circumstances. Previously there wasn't any functionality to accomplish that, which is why I made this PR.

##### 3. Added `EspNvs::iter`

This function allows iterating over all stored keys. I don't need this function, but #340 requests this function and the `erase_all`, so I added it to close that issue with this PR

Regarding the implementation: It seems to work, but I don't know how the API should look like, couldn't find many references.

The main reference was [this example in the esp-idf docs](https://docs.espressif.com/projects/esp-idf/en/v5.5/esp32/api-reference/storage/nvs_flash.html#_CPPv424nvs_entry_find_in_handle12nvs_handle_t10nvs_type_tP14nvs_iterator_t):
```C
// Example of listing all the key-value pairs of any type under specified handle (which defines a partition and namespace)
 nvs_iterator_t it = NULL;
 esp_err_t res = nvs_entry_find_in_handle(<nvs_handle>, NVS_TYPE_ANY, &it);
 while(res == ESP_OK) {
nvs_entry_info_t info;
     nvs_entry_info(it, &info); // Can omit error check if parameters are guaranteed to be non-NULL
     printf("key '%s', type '%d' \n", info.key, info.type);
     res = nvs_entry_next(&it);
 }
 nvs_release_iterator(it);
```
The current code replicates the functionality, ignoring any errors that occur while iterating.

I do not know whether this is desirable or not.

#### Testing

Used it in a separate project, uploaded to the ESP32 and checked for any crashes.
